 contrast effect.\nHe I 10830 \\AA\\ is not strongly affected and absorption signatures are likely\ndiluted, rather than enhanced, by stellar activity. He I 10830 \\AA\\ should thus\nbe considered a priority for probing extended atmospheres, even in the case of\nactive stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Aug 2018 22:22:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-17"}
