uminosities) may have larger absorber median equivalent widths ($1.7\\sigma$)\nand velocity dispersions ($2.5\\sigma$) than galaxy--dwarf groups (disparate\nluminosities). We suggest the observed gas is coupled to the group rather than\nindividual galaxies, forming an intragroup medium. Gas may be deposited into\nthis medium by multiple galaxies via outflowing winds undergoing an\nintergalactic transfer between member galaxies or from tidal stripping of\ninteracting members.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Aug 2018 22:26:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 15 Nov 2018 21:17:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-26"}
